    <StatementCodes>
      <StatementCode>CCSS.Math.Content.4.NF.A.2</StatementCode>
    </StatementCodes>
    <Statements>
      <Statement>Compare two fractions with different numerators and different denominators, e.g., by creating common denominators or numerators, or by comparing to a benchmark fraction such as 1/2. Recognize that comparisons are valid only when the two fractions refer to the same whole. Record the results of comparisons with symbols &amp;gt;, =, or &amp;lt;, and justify the conclusions, e.g., by using a visual fraction model.</Statement>
